## **Introduction**

 According to the Institute for Policy Innovation (2007), because of global and U.S.-based piracy of sound recordings, the U.S. economy loses $12.5 billion in total output and 71,060 jobs annually.

 To address these challenges, the following **secure media** application has been developed to store and manage copyright materials, ensuring that the rights of writers, performers, and other stakeholders are protected (University of Essex Online, 2024).

The application builid is based on the design document: Development Team Project: Design Document by Ming Lee, Bing Hung Lui and Craig Norris.
Any deviations from the original design are explicitly called out along with a corresponding justification as to why.

## **Code Structure and Usage**

### **Application Classes**

![Screenshot 2024-09-04 at 00.42.10.png](data:image/png;base64,)

###**User Class Attributes and Functions**

 Class Attribute | Attribute Description | Addition to Design Document (Yes/No)
--- | --- | ---
 user_id | The unique identifier for the user, typically assigned by the database. | No
username | The username chosen by the user for login and identification purposes. | No
password_hash | The hashed password for the user, used for authentication. | No
role | The role of the user, either admin or regular_user, determining their access level and permissions. | No

Function Name | Function Description | Addition to Design Document (Yes/No)
--- | --- | ---
 __init__ | Initializes a User object with user_id, username, password_hash, and role. | **Yes** - miss on initial design
set_password | Sets the password hash for the user by hashing the provided password. | No
check_password | Checks if the provided password matches the stored password hash. | No
get_role | Returns the role of the user. | No
get_user_id | Returns the user ID. | **Yes** - for enriched functionality
get_username | Returns the username. | **Yes** - for enriched functionality
get_password_hash | Returns the hashed password. | **Yes** - for enriched functionality

###**Administrator Class Attributes and Functions**

Class Attribute | Attribute Description | Addition to Design Document (Yes/No)
--- | --- | ---
None| Inherits attributes from the User class. Administrator does not add new attributes beyond those inherited from User. | No

Function Name | Function Description | Addition to Design Document (Yes/No)
--- | --- | ---
create_artefact | Creates and stores a new artefact in the database through the db_manager. | No
delete_artefact | Deletes an artefact from the database by its ID using the db_manager. | No
view_artefact | Retrieves and returns an artefact from the database by its ID using the db_manager. | **Yes** - miss on initial design
view_logs | Retrieves and prints all logs from the database using the db_manager. | No
view_all_artefacts | Retrieves and returns all artefacts from the database using the db_manager. | **Yes** - miss on initial design

###**RegularUser Class Attributes and Functions**

Class Attribute | Attribute Description | Addition to Design Document (Yes/No)
--- | --- | ---
None| Inherits attributes from the User class. RegularUser does not add new attributes beyond those inherited from User. | No

Function Name | Function Description | Addition to Design Document (Yes/No)
--- | --- | ---
upload_artefact | Uploads and stores a new artefact in the database if the artefact's owner ID matches the user's ID. | No
modify_artefact | Modifies an existing artefact in the database if the artefact's owner ID matches the user's ID. | No
view_artefact | Retrieves and returns an artefact from the database by its ID if the artefact belongs to the user. | **Yes** - for enriched functionality
view_my_artefacts | Retrieves and returns all artefacts owned by the user from the database. | **Yes** - for enriched functionality

###**Artifact Class Attributes and Functions**

Class Attribute | Attribute Description | Addition to Design Document (Yes/No)
--- | --- | ---
artefact_id| The unique identifier for the artefact, typically assigned by the database. | No
title| The title or name of the artefact, used for identification and description purposes. | No
content| The content of the artefact, typically stored as binary data (BLOB). | No
checksum| The checksum value generated for the artefact content to ensure data integrity and detect any changes or corruption. | No
encrypted_content| The encrypted version of the artefact's content for secure storage. | No
timestamps| The timestamp indicating when the artefact was created or last modified. | No
owner_id| The ID of the user who owns the artefact, linking it to the Users table in the database. | No

Function Name | Function Description | Addition to Design Document (Yes/No)
--- | --- | ---
__init__ | Initializes an Artefact object with artefact_id, title, content, owner_id, and generates checksum and timestamps. | **Yes** - miss on initial design
generate_checksum| Generates and returns a checksum for the given data using SHA-256. | No
encrypt_content| Encrypts the artefact's content using the provided the ecryption_manager. | No
decrypt_content| Decrypts and returns the artefact's content using the provided encryption_manager. | No
create_timestamp | Creates and returns a timestamp string representing the current date and time. | **Yes** - rename of function only

###**EncryptionManager Class Attributes and Functions**

Class Attribute | Attribute Description | Addition to Design Document (Yes/No)
--- | --- | ---
key| The encryption key used for encrypting and decrypting data. | No
cipher| The Fernet cipher instance initialized with the encryption key for performing encryption and decryption operations. | No

Function Name | Function Description | Addition to Design Document (Yes/No)
--- | --- | ---
__init__ | Initializes the EncryptionManager with a generated key and cipher instance. | **Yes** - miss on initial design
encrypt| Encrypts the given data using the cipher instance. | No
decrypt| Decrypts the given data using the cipher instance. | No

###**ChecksumManager Class Attributes and Functions**

Class Attribute | Attribute Description | Addition to Design Document (Yes/No)
--- | --- | ---
None| This class does not have attributes but contains static methods for generating and verifying checksums. | No

Function Name | Function Description | Addition to Design Document (Yes/No)
--- | --- | ---
generate_checksum| Static method to generate a checksum for the given data using SHA-256. | No
verify_checksum| Static method to verify if the checksum matches the SHA-256 checksum of the given data. | No

###**TimestampManager Class Attributes and Functions**

Class Attribute | Attribute Description | Addition to Design Document (Yes/No)
--- | --- | ---
None| This class does not have attributes but contains static methods for creating and updating timestamps. | No

Function Name | Function Description | Addition to Design Document (Yes/No)
--- | --- | ---
create_timestamp| Static method to create and return a timestamp string representing the current date and time. | No
update_timestamp| Static method to update and return a timestamp string representing the current date and time. | No

###**DatabaseManager Class Attributes and Functions**

Class Attribute | Attribute Description | Addition to Design Document (Yes/No)
--- | --- | ---
db_name| The name of the database file. | **Yes** - miss on initial design
db_connection| The connection object for interacting with the SQLite database. | No
db_cursor | The cursor object for executing SQL commands and queries on the database. | No

Function Name | Function Description | Addition to Design Document (Yes/No)
--- | --- | ---
__init__ | Initializes the DatabaseManager with a database name, connects to the database, and creates tables if they do not exist. | No
connect_to_db | Connects to the SQLite database and initializes the cursor. | No
create_tables | Creates the Users, Artefacts, and Logs tables in the database if they do not already exist. | No
store_user | Inserts a new user into the Users table. | **Yes** - miss on initial design
store_artefact | Inserts a new artefact into the Artefacts table. | No
retrieve_artefact | Retrieves and returns an artefact from the Artefacts table by its ID. | No
update_artefact | Updates the details of an existing artefact in the Artefacts table. | No
delete_artefact| Deletes an artefact from the Artefacts table by its ID. | No
retrieve_all_artefacts| Retrieves and returns all artefacts from the Artefacts table. | **Yes** - for enriched functionality
retrieve_artefacts_by_user| Retrieves and returns all artefacts owned by a specific user from the Artefacts table. | No
get_user_by_username| Retrieves and returns a user from the Users table by their username. | No
view_logs| Retrieves and prints all logs from the Logs table. | **Yes** - miss on initial design
close | Closes the connection to the SQLite database. | **Yes** - miss on initial design

### **Logger Class**

Class Attribute | Attribute Description | Addition to Design Document (Yes/No)
--- | --- | ---
db_manager | A reference to the DatabaseManager instance used to perform logging operations in the database. | **Yes** - miss on initial design

Function Name | Function Description | Addition to Design Document (Yes/No)
--- | --- | ---
__init__ | Initializes the Logger with a reference to the DatabaseManager instance. | **Yes** - miss on initial design
log_event | Inserts a new log entry into the Logs table with the event details, including user ID, artefact ID, and timestamp. | No
view_logs | Retrieves and prints all logs from the Logs table using the DatabaseManager. | No

### **References**

###References for Libraries Used

**sqlite3:**

Reference: SQLite Consortium. (n.d.). SQLite Documentation. Retrieved from https://www.sqlite.org/docs.html

Usage: Used as a lightweight database engine by the application.

**hashlib:**

Reference: Python Software Foundation. (n.d.). hashlib — Secure hashes and message digests. In Python 3.x Library Documentation. Retrieved from https://docs.python.org/3/library/hashlib.html

Usage: Provides secure hash and message digest algorithms, including SHA-256, used for password hashing.

**datetime:**

Reference: Python Software Foundation. (n.d.). datetime — Basic date and time types. In Python 3.x Library Documentation. Retrieved from https://docs.python.org/3/library/datetime.html

Usage: Used for creating and managing timestamps of key events in the application.

**cryptography:**

Reference: The Cryptography Developers. (n.d.). Cryptography Library Documentation. Retrieved from https://cryptography.io/en/latest/
Usage: Provides the Fernet symmetric encryption scheme for securely encrypting and decrypting content.

**os:**

Reference: Python Software Foundation. (n.d.). os — Miscellaneous operating system interfaces. In Python 3.x Library Documentation. Retrieved from https://docs.python.org/3/library/os.html

Usage: Allows interaction with the underlying operating system, allowing local file upload by the application.   

**getpass:**

Reference: Python Software Foundation. (n.d.). getpass — Portable password input. In Python 3.x Library Documentation. Retrieved from https://docs.python.org/3/library/getpass.html

Usage: Used to securely capture password input from the user without showing charachters on screen.
